
Amazon Comprehend configuration on Windows:

Step 1 : create .aws directory if not exist under user home 
    C:\Users\kristhim\> mkdir .aws 
    cd C:\Users\kristhim\.aws> 
    notepad config
    [default]
    region = us-east-1

Step 2: create Credentials and store the credentials:
    ' Create user in AWS and copy the access_key and secret_access_key 
      then create Credentials file under localhost user home directoy '

    cd C:\Users\kristhim\.aws> 
    notepad credentials
    [default]
    aws_access_key_id = AKIAI6LHSZI2FNDP6AJQ
    aws_secret_access_key = 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

Step 3: Install awscli and boto3 API's 

    ' Install the awscli and boto3 API using pip for the latest python
      to work on amazon comprehend '
    pip install awscli
    pip install boto3


